examples.en: The desk was littered with papers.
The rabbit littered in its small nest.
I can't possibly clean this room with all your clothes littered about!
The park was littered with garbage.
The park was littered with bottles and cans.
Are the horses littered down for the night?
The article was littered with spelling mistakes.
Recent business news has been littered with stories of companies failing.
The region is littered with bridges and buildings named after this great man.
The top of his desk was littered with trinkets that were collected as souvenirs from various vacations.
Paper and popcorn littered the streets after the parade.
After the storm, the ground was littered with twigs and branches.
The floor around the tree was littered with gifts already unwrapped.
Refuse had littered the playground until our volunteer group cleaned it up.
